text: SC Rudolfshügel was a football club from Favoriten, a district of Vienna. The club played from 1902 until 1934. From 1907 until 1927 he played in highest level of Austrian football.Geschichtewiki Wien (German) In 1919 he was runner- up in the championship. The colors were blue and white. The club was named after a elevation between Laaer Berg and Wienerberg. ==References== Category:Football clubs of Vienna Category:1902 establishments in Europe Category:1900s establishments in Austria Category:1934 disestablishments in Europe
